---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy — Latent"
  description="Privacy should be simple. Latent collects as little as possible, uses it only when necessary, and never sells your information."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="legal" id="main">
    <div class="legal-label">Privacy</div>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated 24 July 2026</p>

    <p class="legal-lead">Privacy should be simple. We collect as little as possible, use it only when necessary, and never sell your information.</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>The only information we ask for is your email address, and only if you choose to subscribe to our newsletter or contact us directly.</p>
    <p>This website uses no analytics, no advertising, and no tracking cookies.</p>

    <h2>The newsletter</h2>
    <p>If you subscribe, your email address is managed by Buttondown, our email provider, and used only to send occasional updates about Latent.</p>
    <p>Every email includes an unsubscribe link, and you can leave at any time.</p>

    <h2>Your photographs</h2>
    <p>Latent is a darkroom, not a cloud service.</p>
    <p>Your photographs remain on your device. We do not receive, store, or have access to them &mdash; with one exception: work you deliberately publish to the Moment&rsquo;s community, described below.</p>
    <p>If you choose to use iCloud Photos or iCloud Drive, that synchronization is provided by Apple through your own account and remains under your control.</p>

    <h2>The Moment&rsquo;s community</h2>
    <p>The Moment offers two ways to share, and both are opt-in. Nothing is shared unless you choose to share it.</p>
    <p>A <strong>Circle</strong> is a small, private shared album. Circle accounts, membership, photographs, videos, notes, keeps, and other activity are stored by our community service, hosted on Cloudflare. Access is limited to the people invited into that Circle. Ordinary Circle content is not end-to-end encrypted, which means our service must be able to process it in order to store and deliver it.</p>
    <p><strong>Envelopes</strong> &mdash; the Circle&rsquo;s private messages &mdash; are end-to-end encrypted before they leave the sender&rsquo;s device. Our service stores and delivers the encrypted contents and the routing information needed to carry them, but it does not hold the keys needed to open the contents.</p>
    <p>The <strong>Field</strong> is the Moment&rsquo;s public space. Joining it creates a community account with a handle and a display name, and anything you publish there &mdash; photographs, titles, captions, notes &mdash; becomes visible to other members, associated with your handle. Published work and community accounts are stored by our community service, hosted on Cloudflare. We store only what the feature needs: your account, your profile, what you publish, and the notes, keeps, appreciations, and follows you place.</p>
    <p>Photographs you publish carry no location data, even if location was recorded when they were taken &mdash; that stays on your device.</p>
    <p>If you enable community notifications, your device&rsquo;s push token is registered with our notification service, used only for delivery. If you report content or a member, the report is sent to us and used only for moderation. Blocking someone is recorded so the app can keep their work out of your view.</p>
    <p>You can take back a published post at any time, close a Circle you own, leave a Circle, and delete your community account entirely from inside the app. These actions remove the active copies held by our service, but cannot remove copies another person already saved or shared outside the app.</p>

    <h2>Payments</h2>
    <p>Purchases made through the App Store are processed by Apple.</p>
    <p>Purchases made through our website, including The Lab / OFX plugin, are processed by Paddle.</p>
    <p>We never receive your full payment card details.</p>
    <p>We may receive limited purchase information, such as your name, email address, product purchased, transaction ID, country, and billing or tax status, solely to fulfill your purchase and provide support.</p>

    <h2>Services we rely on</h2>
    <p>We keep our tools few.</p>
    <ul class="legal-list">
      <li>Buttondown for newsletters.</li>
      <li>Apple for Sign in with Apple, push notifications, App Store services, and any Apple Photos or iCloud features you choose to use.</li>
      <li>Paddle for website payments.</li>
      <li>Cloudflare for hosting, domain services, and the Moment&rsquo;s Field and Circle community service.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Each service maintains its own privacy policy.</p>

    <h2>Your choices</h2>
    <p>You may unsubscribe from our newsletter at any time.</p>
    <p>You may also ask us to delete any personal information we hold by writing to <a href="mailto:support@latentritual.com">support@latentritual.com</a>.</p>
    <p>Depending on where you live, you may have additional rights over your personal information. We will honor those rights where applicable.</p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>Latent is not intended for children under the age of 16, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from them.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>If this policy changes, we will update this page and revise the date above.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about privacy? <a href="mailto:support@latentritual.com">support@latentritual.com</a></p>

    <a class="legal-back" href="/">← Back to Latent</a>
  </main>
  <Footer />

  <style>
    .legal { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 140px 24px 120px; }
    .legal-label { font-family: var(--font-label); font-weight: 300; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.28em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber-dim); margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .legal h1 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 300; font-size: 40px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--text-bright); margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .legal-updated { font-family: var(--font-body); font-style: italic; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-ghost); margin-bottom: 48px; }
    .legal-lead { font-size: 18px !important; line-height: 1.75 !important; color: var(--text) !important; }
    .legal-list { margin: 0 0 14px; padding-left: 20px; }
    .legal-list li { font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 300; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .legal h2 { font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 400; font-size: 21px; color: var(--text-bright); margin: 40px 0 12px; }
    .legal p { font-family: var(--font-body); font-weight: 300; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .legal a { color: var(--amber); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light); transition: color 0.3s ease, text-shadow 0.6s ease, border-color 0.6s ease; }
    .legal a:hover { color: var(--text-bright); text-shadow: 0 0 16px rgba(232, 196, 160, 0.5); border-color: transparent; }
    .legal-back { display: inline-block; margin-top: 48px; font-family: var(--font-label); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber-dim); border-bottom: none; }
    .legal-back:hover { color: var(--text-bright); text-shadow: 0 0 16px rgba(232, 196, 160, 0.5); }
  </style>
</Base>
